[ name(Mereki Cole — Wiradjuri name "Mereki" meaning peacemaker 
  given to her at First Change in recognition of her Children-of-Gaia 
  affinity; surname Cole from her Anglo-Australian father's 
  side); status(Children of Gaia continental peacemaker 
  representative for southeastern Australia since 2018; 
  observer-status delegate at quarterly Truce Council; 
  diplomatic mediator for cross-tribal and cross-supernatural 
  disputes); tribe(Children of Gaia); rank(Adren); 
  auspice(Theurge); age(38); pronouns(she/her); ]

[ background(Wiradjuri-Anglo-Australian, born Wagga Wagga 1987 
  to a Wiradjuri mother and Anglo-Australian father (Diana 
  Cole's nephew); Children-of-Gaia heritage on the paternal 
  side going back four generations; First Change 2005 at age 
  18 during a Children-of-Gaia ritual at the family's regional 
  NSW caern; spent her early operational career in Children-of-Gaia 
  cross-tribal mediation work across NSW and Victoria; took 
  the continental representative role 2018 when her predecessor 
  ascended to Continental Sept Council senior position; based 
  primarily in regional Tasmania (the Children of Gaia 
  Australian sept centres in Cradle Mountain region) but 
  travels frequently to Melbourne and other mainland 
  diplomatic locations); ]

[ appearance(Tall for an Australian woman, mixed-heritage 
  features that read as Indigenous-Australian to Australian 
  observers, dark hair worn in a long single braid, dark 
  eyes lined with the deliberate calm of long Theurge ritual 
  practice; perpetually in earth-tone clothing — soft layered 
  garments, woven Australian-fibre cloth (her own mother's 
  weaving), sensible boots; carries a small leather pouch 
  containing ritual-significant items including emu-feather, 
  river-stones from her country, and a small carved wooden 
  pendant from her grandmother; the Theurge-auspice's 
  spirit-perception shows in the way her eyes occasionally 
  go briefly distant during conversation when her perception 
  catches Umbra movement); ]

[ Garou Form Capacity: All five forms; specialty in homid-form 
  for diplomatic work and in spirit-form (Theurges have access 
  to additional ritual-form capacities); avoids combat-form 
  except in defensive emergencies); ]

[ disciplines_equivalent(Theurge auspice Gifts: Spirit Speech, 
